title: Grateful Dead Live at Philadelphia Civic Center on 1984-04-21
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, West L.A. Fadeaway, Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Don't Need Love-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Further Recording information This show was recorded from about the 14th row center/left of the isle. In the Civic Center an isle ran right down the middle of the venue so it was impossible to get an FOB dead center. Ross (?) was the lead taper along with his buddy. They combined their systems together and made nice recordings of the shows. I met Ross at SPAC in 1983 while recording that show from the lawn. I believe he was from Boston and went to school in Berkely. For the entire run I had between 8th and 15th row seats, which were used for all the recordings. At times there were up to 12 decks patched out and daisy chained.

I should add that although this was recorded with Naks and Senn 421's IMO, this recording stands along with the best audience pulls from this night. Do not rule this recording out based solely on the mics used. This is a great example of how where you are set up can often trump equipment. The sound stage is deep and wide and the timbres are much more pure and organic then systems set up back further in the hall.

Finally, a big thank you for the work on making this a seamless show. The extra bonus is now I get to down load and enjoy the extra work that went into making this pull seamless!!!!
